// CONTENT:
// Product Guide: HAFT EnginesComponent ID: F-COMPUTE-ENGClassification: Execution BackendsAuthor: AI/Compute Team1. Vision & PurposeHAFT Engines are the specialized execution backends for the Hyper-Adaptive Flux Tensor. They are responsible for generating the lowest-level machine code for mathematical operations.2. Technical Replacement SpecsReplaces: OpenBLAS, MKL, CUDA kernels.Backends:JIT-CPU: Generates site-specific AVX-512 code.Vulkan/SPIR-V: For cross-vendor GPU execution.Tensor-Core: Native support for specialized AI hardware.3. FeaturesOperator Fusion: Merges multiple mathematical operations into a single kernel to save memory bandwidth.Shape Specialization: If a tensor is always [1, 512], the engine generates a kernel hardcoded for those dimensions.4. Why this existsGeneric libraries (like BLAS) are optimized for large matrices. HAFT Engines optimize for the specific matrices used in your code.
